In Need for Speed: The Run you compete all over America.
Review
A journey, at first unconcerned, is complicated by a series of improper carelessness of a routine trip during tomorrow's shift.
To some extent it was possible to meet expectations, but this is useless, if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new installment, to which the title is added The Run, raised high expectations already before its premiere.
He promised to give new air to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, in the wake of what has been shown, it appears as a game that should not end up being an action genre again.
We are also curious about how the inserted scenes would look, where the main character gets out of the car and walks on his own foot.
As is often the case in NFS series, the results don’t vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in total count points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already been appearing in the series for years.
In reality, they cannot even be called errors, but rather it is the incomprehensible disappointment of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race all over America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the chart is equivalent to that of previous installments in the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But the desert walk, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
In the mountains, be careful that you are not buried in a flood.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of rivals (normal in a classic race), then you try to gain time (timed classic duel) and then you are waiting for a duel against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this the police sometimes appear, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button just at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It’s surprising, though, that there’s a lot less scenery in the game than you’d expect (specifically there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of previous episodes.
That means it’s no longer a big deal, but it can’t be said to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with enough action is quite suitable for this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, all in order.
Problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, collisions are no longer the same.
From such games you can not expect to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, so not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight overtaking or circulating the car with normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
Resets are scheduled in such a way that when you suffer an accident or leave the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five resets are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it’s just a help in case something goes wrong, but it’s not very trustworthy.
Sometimes, even resetting doesn’t help, it just helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, although you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It’s the same when you arrive, because it’s programmed because “surprise” will always happen in front of your noses.
The opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will arrive at places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always advance you in the same place.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must come before you, at whatever price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come in front, so at first you can pop the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you right away.
And it’s a shame, because although the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter if the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so it doesn’t fit the boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during races.
You have to be attentive to the gasoline suppliers next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough of what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example, on mountain roads with curves.
In addition to the main narrative thread there is also a parallel thread of challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver is given several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and makes other community features available.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you get to the subway tunnel (pass), where you start to run in the dark on the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and suddenly, from behind you arrives the subway convoy and you are taken in front of nothing else.
In the writing we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game nobody even thought a little or if the real authors take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects are in most cases enjoyable, sometimes even superb.
What a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This especially affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feel of Need for Speed: The Run is pretty confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble saying that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
The fun is guaranteed, but be prepared because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
The Carolina University choirs will participate in the "Students of Velvet" concert.
The joint celebration of International Students’ Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival Festa Academica.
During the event, twenty choirs from high schools and colleges will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
“Carolina University has a high stake in the festival.”
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the committee of the festival there is the rector Václav Hampl," said the head of the organization, Jakub Aloun.
The summit of the entire festival is free admission for all audiences to the concert of the high school choirs, which will be held on March 17 at 2 p.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program features Czech jazz player Karel R?i?ka and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady the concert "Students of Velvet" will be held, in which university choirs will participate, including the Carolina University Choir.
The aim of the Academic Festival is not only to celebrate the International Students’ Day and commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choral music to the public at the highest level and promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler High School Institute.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of the Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The festival will take place between November 16th and 20th between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised student shows and morning concerts.
Interested parties can find more information on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
