Evicted a busy farm where macro parties were held
The invaders had taken over 11 of the 13 floors of the building, in Balmes, 51
The 12 occupants left the estate at noon yesterday without offering resistance.
Everything seems to indicate that the nightmare lived by the neighbors of 51 of Balmes Street has come to an end.
Twelve people left yesterday at noon voluntarily the property they occupied illegally, and where they organized macro parties that despaired the neighborhood, by court order and without the need for police intervention.
When the operation was finished, the door latch was changed to prevent the situation from repeating.
“There will be access control from now on,” the administrator said.
The squatters, who had invaded 11 of the 13 floors of the building - the rest are inhabited - took all the electrical installation and part of the water, in addition to painting the walls and leaving waste of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
The first three floors were the scene of crowded parties, which lasted up to two days and despaired the tenants.
Next to the building is a nightclub, Balmes 51, which has also been damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that since the building was occupied the business has fallen by 80%.
The owner of the discotheque points out that the invaders of the estate were unfair competition, as they sold the cups for three euros, while in the discotheque they are worth 10.
In addition, the owner of the entertainment venue had had to respond to noise complaints, while, according to him, the inconveniences are not caused by the customers of the discotheque, but by the inhabitants of the busy house and, above all, the attendees of the parties that were organized there, which had increased their frequency and intensity in recent weeks, according to the angry neighbors of the area.
The person in charge of the discotheque explained that the inconveniences were so great that he even reached an agreement with the owner of the property and nine months ago he “forgives” the rent.
