This was the work of the caleño who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A lophoscopist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a lophoscopist from the Cali ITC went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the FARC’s top boss: “Alfonso Cano”, through the matching of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lophoscopists working in the ITC section, Eliazar Gonzalez, a Puerto Tejada man who has been working in the judicial investigation area for 21 years, was on duty that week.
At the beginning of his career, Gonzalez worked in municipalities of the Chocó, where he often had to go to the jungle for more than five days to reach the place where the corpses were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after taking the corresponding courses, specialized in lofoscopy, which is the study of friction skin, that is, the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against the alias Alfonso Cano Eliazar was warned to wear minimum clothes for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for the Cauca in a helicopter from Palmyra.
He knew he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected of being the man leading the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to carry the decadactyl card of Guillermo Leon Saenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the research team at the site where the corpse was located, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a local farmer, without glasses and much thinner.
But the footprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter, and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the corpse’s fingerprints to those of the card.
His eye did not fail: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was the FARC’s top chief.
In Search of the Footprint
For a Sijín de Cali typist, the recognition given by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar González at the press conference for the operation against “Cano” is very significant.
A lot of people don’t know about our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin for error, that can become key in solving crimes.
Apart from the identification of corpses, lophoscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many criminals have false ballots or no papers.
We take the fingerprint and look for them in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, it was up to him to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to take out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to take a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts,” he recalled.
The fingerprints can also rule out or reassert suspects in homicide cases.
They recently found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a family member could be suspected of the crime and, indeed, a footprint on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the killer, it does place him at the crime scene.
A CTI fingerprinter explained that in objects "the fingerprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the prints are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
“The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians,” the ITC expert said.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI television show.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes a footprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective matching is performed.
